data.name: LineDiagram
desc: specifies line, spline and symbol diagrams.

properties.name: Lines
desc: determines if the chart type has lines connecting the data points or contains just symbols.

properties.name: SplineOrder
desc: specifies the power of the polynomials used for spline calculation
This property is only valid for B-splines

properties.name: SplineResolution
desc: determines the number of sampling points of a spline

properties.name: SplineType
desc: determines if the chart is a spline-chart type and specifies the type of splines.
You can set the following values:

properties.name: SymbolBitmap
desc: Set this property to a graphic object which is then used as symbol for all series.

properties.name: SymbolBitmapURL
desc: Set this property to any valid URL that points to a graphic file.
This graphic is then used as symbol for all series.
When you query this value you get an internal URL of the embedded graphic.

properties.name: SymbolSize
desc: specifies the size of symbols in 1/100th of a millimeter.

properties.name: SymbolType
desc: determines which type of symbols are displayed.
In this interface, only the two values ChartSymbolType.NONE and ChartSymbolType.AUTO are supported. Later versions may support the selection of the symbols shape.
If you set this property to ChartSymbolType.AUTO, you can change the symbol shape for objects supporting the service ChartDataPointProperties or ChartDataRowProperties.
